{% image src="/media/2017/02/anbi.png" align="center" /%}
Quina Care Foundation is a 'Algemeen Nut Beogende Instelling' (ANBI – Public Benefit Organization). This means that under certain circumstances, following the Dutch tax-law, donations are tax-deductible:

##### Donation

A donation can be deducted from your taxable income if it falls within 1% and 10% of your threshold income.

##### Periodical donation

You could also sponsor us for a longer period of time, which provides more certainty for us to continue the work of Quina Care. If you are willing to sponsor us for a 5-year period, your donation will be tax deductible in its entirety. To make use of this scheme all you need is a contract between yourself and Quina Care, which is possible without the involvement of a solicitor. You can download the necessary form [here](https://quinacare.org/document/Overeenkomst.pdf). Once completed, you can send it to us after which it will be signed by us and sent back to you. You can send the form to the following e-mail address: treasurer@quinacare.org

If you have any questions or if you would like further information, please do not hesitate to contact us.
